All Implemented Interfaces:
StdContainer<Pair<T,Record<T>>>, StdMap<T,Record<T>>, StdRandom<Pair<T,Record<T>>,T>, StdRandomStartWith<Pair<T,Record<T>>,T>, StdRandomUnique<Pair<T,Record<T>>,T>, StdSequence<Pair<T,Record<T>>>, Index<T>
public class IdentityIndex<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
extends UniqueIndex<T,T>
implements StdMap<T,Record<T>>

The index is sorted in order of data-type identity

(Depends on Comparable<T>). 
 
The case of sequential access using CompatibleIterable (simple)
 IdentityIndex<MyData> identity = (IdentityIndex<MyData>)multiIndex.index(0);
 for ( Pair<MyData,Record<MyData>> p : new CompatibleIterable<Pair<MyData,Record<MyData>>>(identity)){
   Record<MyData> r = p.second;
   MyData d = r.get();
        :  
 }
 
 
The case of sequential access using raw iterator(flexible).
 IdentityIndex<MyData> identity = (IdentityIndex<MyData>)multiIndex.index(0);
 for ( StdIterator<Pair<MyData,Record<MyData>>> it = identity.begin(),
                                             itend = identity.end();
       ! it.equals(itend);
       it.next())
 {
   Record<MyData> r = it.get().second;
   MyData d = r.get();
        :  
 }

Author:
hiroaki.kubota@mail.rakuten.co.jp
